               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Or_5939-item1">
                     <author key="person_f1421">
                        <persName type="supplied" subtype="aut">Ibn Qāsim al-Kīlānīابن قاسم الكيلاني</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7757">شرح فصول أبقراط</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7757">Commentary on Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7757">Sharḥ Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in the British Library</note>
                     <note>This is a thematically arranged commentary. It lacks the first few folios as well as the several folios at the end; it begins in the middle of the introduction, and ends in the middle of comm. on lemma i. 5. It has no chapter numbering. The last few folios are bound in the wrong order. After f.217, the correct order is 218, 224, 225, 223, 219, 220, 221, 222.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
